== English ==
=== Etymology ===
Unclear; possibly a corruption of Italian ''deletto'', "delight", or English "diddle"; or possibly derived from "Dil Doul", as in e.g. "''The Maids Complaint for want of a Dil Doul''", a song found in the library of [[w:Samuel Pepys|Samuel Pepys]].

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɪldəʊ|-ɪldəʊ]]

=== Noun ===
'''dildo'''

# An artificial [[phallus]] ([[penis]]), particularly for [[sexual]] uses, that may or may not appear [[realistic]].
# An idiot.

